e,94.7%and 92.5%of the population in China has a time cost of less than 1 h in obtaining hospital and school services,respectively.Counties with low accessibility to hospitals and schools were highly coupled with poor areas and ecological function regions,with the time cost incurred in these areas being more than twice that experienced in non-poor and non-ecological areas.Furthermore,the cumulative time cost incurred by the bottom 20%of counties(by GDP)from access to hospital and school services reached approximately 80%of the national total.Low-GDP counties were compelled to suffer disproportionately increased time costs to acquire health and education services compared with high-GDP counties.The accessibil-ity metrics proposed in this study are highly related to SDGs 3 and 4,and they can serve as auxiliary data that can be used to enhance the evaluation of SDG outcomes.The analysis of the uneven distribution of health and education services in China can help identify areas with backward public services and may contribute to targeted and efficient policy interventions.","authors":[{"name":"Shan Hu"},{"name":"Rongtian Zhao"},{"name":"Yuxue Cui"},{"name":"Die Zhang"},{"name":"Yong Ge"}],"home_page_url":"http://m.qikan.cqvip.com/Article/ArticleDetail?id=7109857108","publication_date":"2023-01-01","journal":{"name":"ã€Šåœ°ç†å­¦ä¸å¯æŒç»­æ€§(è‹±æ–‡)ã€‹"},"citation_datas":[{"format":0,"citation":"Shan Hu,Rongtian Zhao,Yuxue Cui,Die Zhang,Yong Ge. \"Identifying the uneven distribution of health and education services in China using open geospatial data.\" ã€Šåœ°ç†å­¦ä¸å¯æŒç»­æ€§(è‹±æ–‡)ã€‹ 2(2023)."},{"format":1,"citation":"Shan Hu,Rongtian Zhao,Yuxue Cui,Die Zhang,Yong Ge. (2023). Identifying the uneven distribution of health and education services in China using open geospatial data. ã€Šåœ°ç†å­¦ä¸å¯æŒç»­æ€§(è‹±æ–‡)ã€‹(2)."}],"unique_id":"Identifying the uneven distribution of health and education services in China using open geospatial dataShan Hu,Rongtian Zhao,Yuxue Cui